Dangerous escaped criminals have been roaming the streets for more than a month. Two offenders fled Tshwane’s Kgosi Mampuru centre on the 9th of December last year. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Dangerous escaped criminals have been roaming the streets for more than a month. Two offenders escaped from the fled Kgosi Mampuru II Correctional Centre in Pretoria last month. READ: Manhunt underway for escaped prisoners in Pretoria One offender was serving 21 years for various violent crimes, including rape and kidnapping, and the other had a 20-year sentence for housebreaking crimes. Correctional Services says it's working with law enforcement agencies to make sure that the two are brought back behind bars.